<br>
Armsman going crush spec to slash/thrust at 50. Gets 77 free points. (Easy way to autotrain without being gimped/PLed).<br>
<br>
Armsman going from slash/thrust to crush at 50. Loses 77 free points.<br>
<br>
Now if you autotrained those points, no problem. If you spent real points on them, you're now 77 points in the hole. They didn't want to screw over people who used autotrain. So instead they screwed over prople who didn't use autotrain.<br>
<br>
&quot;Simple&quot; fix. Add additional respec commands for line and full. These would reset all your skills to 0 (you would not get autotrain). And would give you however many points you should have attained by that level.<br>
<br>
Granted this only affects tank classes really. Since afaik they are the only ones who get auto-trained in only SOME of their primary lines (e.g. slash and thrust, but not crush).<br>
<br>
Another solution is to add auto-training to crush, since I don't see any real reason this is the case.<br>
<br>
But hell I'd love to have started as crush myself to get those 77 free points (and to have been a saracen, ah well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
